r s BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LAD     10-02 0739
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KINGS' THOMAS CONTACTED BY FOX'S WELTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Sacramento Kings president John Thomas said he was
contacted by Rick Welts, president of Fox Sports Enterprises, and
wouldn't rule out joining one of baseball's most prestigious
organizations.
</P>
<P>
   Welts called Thomas to talk about becoming the next Dodgers
president. The two are longtime business associates from Welts'
tenure in the NBA. Thomas is one of six candidates to replace
recently fired Dodgers president and CEO Bob Graziano.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's incredibly flattering to be mentioned in the context of
the Dodgers with Fox and Rick Welts, but all my focus is with
what's going on with the Sacramento Kings,'' Thomas said Friday.
``We have one of the most exciting teams in the NBA and we're
getting ready for the season. It's the first day of training camp
and all my focus is on that.''
</P>
<P>
   Welts' and Thomas' relationship goes back to their days together
in the NBA. Welts worked in the NBA office under David Stern and
Thomas was working for the Houston Rockets and Comets (WNBA).
Thomas, who accepted the job as president of the Kings, Sacramento
Monarchs (WNBA) and Sacramento Knights (Arena Football) in July,
also worked for the Minnesota Timberwolves and Seattle Mariners.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas said it was too early to tell if he would interview with
Welts, but said the two had a strong working relationship.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm trying to be sensitive to the issue,'' Thomas said. ``I
don't want to speculate on the future. The recent developments down
there ... are flattering.''
</P>
<P>
   Sheff shutdown?: After playing half of the season with pain in
his shoulders and knees, left fielder Gary Sheffield's season may
be over after hitting a homer and driving in three runs Friday
against Houston.
</P>
<P>
   His two-run single in the third inning also enabled him to
eclipse the 100-RBI mark for the third time in his career, and the
first time since 1996 when he drove in a career-high 120 with
Florida. His first-inning homer also tied him with Karros for the
team lead with 34 homers.
</P>
<P>
   ``I may not play him again this year,'' Dodgers manager Davey
Johnson said. ``With his shoulder and his knees, I don't know.... A
very tough year for a lot of us on this club, his perseverance has
been a bright spot. If everybody on this club took his approach in
every aspect of the game, we'd be a lot better.''
</P>
<P>
   If Johnson doesn't use his all-star left fielder again,
Sheffield would join Duke Snider (1955) as the only Dodger to bat
at least .300 in a season, hit 30 homers and reach the century mark
in RBI (101), runs (103) and walks (101).
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll go with whatever he says,'' Sheffield said. ``If he
doesn't want to play me, I don't have a problem with that. You have
to see what other guys can do.''
</P>
<P>
   They hate L.A.: The New York airwaves are scorching the Dodgers,
and this time it has nothing to do with leaving Brooklyn. With the
Mets engaged in a playoff battle they are frittering away (for the
second straight year), the folks in the Big Apple are miffed that
Dodgers' ace Kevin Brown won't start in Sunday's season finale
against Houston. It's the last regular season game in the
Astrodome.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson said he still isn't sure who will start, but signs point
toward Robinson Checo. Johnson previously said Brown's season ended
with his Wednesday loss in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   ``He wants to go, but to me, our year is over,'' Johnson said.
``I don't feel comfortable, with the year he's had, bring my ace
back on three days' rest. I think it's one of those things if
you're trying to the playoffs (you try it), but it's another thing
to stress him.''
</P>
<P>
   FYI: Right-hander Ismael Valdes won't return to the team this
season. Valdes has been in his native Mexico since Monday. He went
there after learning his father was involved in a car accident....
Eric Karros' first-inning single extended his hitting streak to 11
games, tying the longest by a Dodger this season. Adrian Beltre,
Mark Grudzielanek and Sheffield also hit in 11 straight.... The
Dodgers announced Beltre and catcher Angel Pena will play winter
ball in the Dominican Republic, former Santa Paula High and Ventura
College star Brent Cookson will play in Mexico, Matt Herges will
pitch in Venezuela and Onan Masaoka and Jeff Williams will pitch in
the Arizona Fall League.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-02-99 0142EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19991002.0015 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-02 01:42 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4362 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s BC-BKN-PIPPEN-TRADE-NYT &LR;      10-02 0577
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-PIPPEN-TRADE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PIPPEN GETS HIS WISH AS ROCKETS TRADE HIM
</HEADLINE>
   (rk) 
 By MIKE WISE   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   A disgruntled Scottie Pippen, who skewered his teammate Charles
Barkley this week and seemed to be campaigning mightily for a trade
from the Houston Rockets, got his wish Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   According to a Western Conference executive who spoke on
condition of anonymity, the Rockets will send Pippen to the
Portland Trail Blazers for six role players.
</P>
<P>
   Eight months after signing a five-year, $67 million deal and
moving from the Chicago Bulls to the Rockets, Pippen is expected to
be dealt for Kelvin Cato, Walt Williams, Stacey Augmon, Ed Gray,
Brian Shaw and Carlos Rogers.
</P>
<P>
   Barring salary-cap complications, the deal is expected to be
made official at the league's Manhattan office Saturday, the
executive said. It comes two days before National Basketball
Association teams open training camp for the 1999-2000 season and
several days after Pippen verbally eviscerated Barkley.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley started the ruckus. Saying he sacrificed to make salary
cap room on the Rockets for Pippen, Barkley knocked Pippen. ``For
him to want to leave after one year, it disappointed me greatly,''
he said. ``The Rockets went out of their way to get Scottie, and
the fans have treated him well, so I was just disappointed in
him.''
</P>
<P>
   That was benign compared to Pippen's barrage on ESPN: ``I
probably should've listened to Michael a year ago when he said that
Charles will never win a championship because he doesn't show any
dedication,'' Pippen said. ``He's a very selfish guy. He doesn't
show the desire to want to win.''
</P>
<P>
   Pippen had openly pushed for a trade to the Lakers ever since
his former coach Phil Jackson was given the Lakers job last June.
Pippen said he would never consider apologizing to Barkley.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wouldn't give Charles Barkley an apology at gunpoint,'' he
said. ``He can never expect an apology from me. If anything, he
owes me an apology'' for the way he played. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Rockets' owner, Les Alexander, instructed team officials to
listen to offers for Pippen, but not to pull the trigger on a deal
until all offers had been weighed. Cato and Williams were the only
players Houston was genuinely interested in, a Rockets official
said on condition of anonymity. Because of Pippen's $14 million
salary for this season, a six-for-one deal was the only way the
trade could be consummated.
</P>
<P>
   Denver had offered Nick Van Exel, even though the Rockets
engaged in an 11-player deal in August _ the largest-player
transaction in league history _ to acquire rookie point guard Steve
Francis from Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen, 34, asked to be traded several times while with the
Bulls during their championship run, and always ended up mending
relationships and coming back.
</P>
<P>
   The trade was reported by the Houston Chronicle earlier this
week. KRIV-TV in Houston reported Friday night the deal is
imminent.
</P>
<P>
   If approved by the league, the trade bolsters Portland standing
in the Western Conference playoff picture. Already the Trail
Blazers dealt for veteran shooting guard Steve Smith in the
off-season and rid themselves of Isaiah Rider and Jim Jackson.
</P>
<P>
   With Damon Stoudamire at point guard, Smith at shooting guard,
Pippen at small forward, Brian Grant at power forward and Arvydas
Sabonis, Detlef Schrempf and Rasheed Wallace playing major minutes,
the Blazers appear on course to contend with San Antonio.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-02-99 0142EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19991002.0016 </DOCNO>
