</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 1 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   MILLENNIUM-DOME (Greenwich, England) _ When the first stanchions
went up in 1997 for the mammoth cupola being erected here to mark
the millennium, the image that rose in the mind's eye of many
Britons had the pale coloration and oversized contours of a white
elephant. ``The millennium fiasco,'' The Evening Standard called
it. Now, though, the $1.2 billion Millennium Dome has developed a
more alluring fragrance, and become a beast that Britons seem eager
to climb aboard for their ride into the new century. By Warren
Hoge.
</P>
