<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-EVANDER _ Evander Holyfield appears to have history on his
side as he prepares for his heavyweight rematch fight against
Lennox Lewis on Nov. 13. Holyfield has always fared well in
rematches, defeating Mike Tyson, Riddick Bowe, Michael Moorer and
George Foreman when meeting for the second time. Holyfield believes
the key to his success in rematches in his ability to learn from
his mistakes in the first fight. Considering that Holyfield barely
gained a draw in his first fight with Lewis, there are many
mistakes to correct heading into the next fight. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
