<P>
   Here are the news stories the Los Angeles Daily News plans to
move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of Oct. 3
and thereafter. For questions about stories, please contact
Elizabeth Ferry Slocum at the Daily News at (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   SUNSHINE-LANDFILL (Los Angeles) _ The nation's biggest landfill
could soon open in Los Angeles' San Fernando Valley if the Los
Angeles City Council gives its approval _ and the council is giving
every indication that it will do so. But the dump's neighbors are
fighting the proposal on every front. By Troy Anderson. (Will move
in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTHY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Henry Rabow, who observed his
100th birthday Friday in a Tarzana retirement home, is reportedly
the most popular guy around. By Dennis McCarthy. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BEATTY-PRESIDENCY _ On Wednesday evening, C-SPAN was just one of
dozens of media outlets flocking to cover a Beverly Hills speech by
Warren Beatty ... an actor who last year played a senator whose
remarks in Beverly Hills and several other campaign stops were
being covered by C-SPAN. We'll take a look at Beatty's stand on
issues and how that compares with the fictional ``Bulworth,'' which
Beatty wrote and starred in. By Marla Matzer. (Will move in the
``a'' national, ``e'' entertainment and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
