MCCAIN (Undated) _ John McCain wasn't just kicking off his
presidential campaign last week, he was celebrating his rise to the
top of the pack of GOP candidates who aren't named George W. Bush.
For all he had to celebrate, though, McCain still had this to
ponder: There are a hundred ways for Bush to win the nomination.
For McCain, there are just a few. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move
